:::< from {{etyl|sa}} {{term|रूप्य|lang=sa|sc=Deva|tr=rūpya||[[wrought]] silver}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The common name for the [[monetary]] [[currency|currencies]] used in modern [[India]], [[Pakistan]], [[Nepal]], [[Sri Lanka]], [[Seychelles]], or [[Mauritius]].
# A silver coin, circulating in [[India]] 16th–20th centuries, weighing 170–180&nbsp;[[troy grain]]s (180&nbsp;troy grains from 1833) or one [[tola]].

